On German-American Day, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. honors the over 40 million Americans with German heritage and recognizes their contributions to the United States. German Americans have played a significant role in American history, from founding the first German settlement in 1683 to fighting for freedom in the Revolutionary War. They have also been influential in various sectors and communities, forming strong bonds between Germany and the United States. The partnership between the two countries is crucial in addressing global challenges and upholding shared values such as freedom and democracy. The proclamation designates October 6, 2023, as German-American Day and encourages all Americans to celebrate the rich history and contributions of German Americans.